TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dixit, Avinash
AU  - Londregan, John
T1  - Ideology, Tactics, and Efficiency in Redistributive Politics*
PY  - 1998
Y1  - 1998/05/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355398555667
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 113
IS  - 2
SP  - 497
EP  - 529
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We model the electoral politics of redistribution when voters and parties care about inequality in addition to their private concerns for consumption and votes, respectively. Ideological concerns about income redistribution lead each party to adopt a general proportional income tax, adjusted to appeal to the ideological leanings of high “clout” groups, with disproportionately many “swing” voters, which the parties also ply with pork-barrel projects. Our results relate to “Director's Law,” which says that redistributive politics favors middle classes at the expense of both rich and poor.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355398555667
ER  - 



